benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/cbaRebalancing - Rebalance account CBA

covered: Valid Request: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/cbaRebalancing returns 204 for successful rebalance (TC01–TC03)
Non-Existing Resource: TC08 validates 400 for invalid/non-existent account
Concurrency: TC18 high concurrency; TC07 multiple CBA-impacting transactions
Header Validation coverage: presence of required header (TC01/TC03) and tests for missing/empty/whitespace/null headers (TC10, TC11, TC25, TC26)
Optional headers handling: TC02 tests with optional headers (X-Killbill-Reason, X-Killbill-Comment)
gaps: Authorization: no test for unauthorized access (invalid/missing or invalid token) leading to 401/403
Rate Limiting: no tests for throttling or rate limit behavior
Caching Behavior: no tests for ETag/Cache-Control and caching validation
500 Internal Server Error: no test simulating database failure producing 500
Payload validation: if a request body/payload exists, no tests for invalid payload types or partial updates
Audit/logging validation: no tests specifically asserting audit/log outputs
recommendations: Add tests for authorization failures (401/403) to cover unauthorized access scenarios
Add rate-limiting/throttling scenarios to exercise API under load
Add caching header checks (ETag, Cache-Control) and verify caching behavior
Add a 500 Internal Server Error scenario to cover database/service failure handling
If PUT supports a request body, add tests for invalid payloads and partial update behavior
Consider additional end-to-end regression tests to validate stability across related CBA scenarios
